25|$|In July 1948, {{a strike}} was averted {{at the last}} minute as the SAG and major {{producers}} agreed upon a new collective bargaining contract. The major points agreed upon included: full <b>union</b> <b>shop</b> for actors to continue, negotiations for films sent direct to TV, producers could not sue an actor for breach of contract if they strike (but the guild could only strike when the contract expires).|$|E
